<div id="stephanie-benedetto" class="js-filtered-profile g50-profile-container" data-category-list="business-tech ">

	
	<div class="g50-profile g50-profile--stephanie-benedetto" >

		<!-- label (like for sponsors) -->
		
		<!-- person's name -->
		<h2 class="g50-profile__name">
			<span>Stephanie Benedetto</span>
		</h2>

		<!-- person's position & city -->
					<div class="g50-profile__stats"><p>COFOUNDER &amp; CEO, QUEEN OF RAW<br />
NEW YORK, NEW YORK</p>
</div>
		
		<!-- person's excerpt -->
		<h3 class="g50-profile__excerpt"><p>This scrappy entrepreneur is trimming textile waste</p>
</h3>

		<!-- guest author stuff -->
		
		<!-- person's photo -->
					<div class="g50-profile__photo">
				<img src="https://grist.files.wordpress.com/2020/03/stephanie-benedetto-1.jpg?w=560" class="g50-profile__photo-img wp-post-image" alt="" data-noattr="1" srcset="https://grist.files.wordpress.com/2020/03/stephanie-benedetto-1.jpg?w=560 560w, https://grist.files.wordpress.com/2020/03/stephanie-benedetto-1.jpg?w=1120 1120w, https://grist.files.wordpress.com/2020/03/stephanie-benedetto-1.jpg?w=330 330w, https://grist.files.wordpress.com/2020/03/stephanie-benedetto-1.jpg?w=768 768w" sizes="(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px" />				<!-- photo credit -->
							</div>
		
		<!-- person's content -->
		<div class="g50-profile__body">
			<p>According to Stephanie Benedetto, around $120 billion worth of the fabrics created every year go unused, generally winding up tossed or burned. So she created an internet matchmaker to improve the market for deadstock, the excess fabric piled up in warehouses around the globe. On her blockchain-powered Queen of Raw website, sellers can post excess inventory, and buyers can sort by fabric type and price to get steep discounts.</p>
<p>Textile production uses tons of water, so in the last quarter of 2019 alone, she says, Queen of Raw’s 130,000 users have saved over 1 billion gallons of water that would have gone into making new material.</p>
<p>Going forward, Benedetto plans to offer similar services to industries like aviation and computer electronics. “Any business that has a supply chain creates waste,” she says. “It&#8217;s just a supply–demand mismatch and we can correct it.”</p>
			<div class="g50-follow g50-follow--hide-desktop">
				<a class="g50-follow__link" href="https://www.instagram.com/queenofraw/" rel="noopener" target="_blank"><i class="fab fa-instagram g50-follow__icon"></i>Follow Stephanie Benedetto</a>			</div>
		</div>

		<!-- person's cagetgories -->
		<div class="g50-profile__categories">
			<span>Category: </span>
												<button data-category="business-tech">
						Business &amp; Tech					</button>
																</div>

		<div class="g50-profile__footer">
			<div class="g50-follow g50-follow--hide-mobile">
				<a class="g50-follow__link" href="https://www.instagram.com/queenofraw/" rel="noopener" target="_blank"><i class="fab fa-instagram g50-follow__icon"></i>Follow Stephanie Benedetto</a>			</div>

