<div id="tony-bova" class="js-filtered-profile g50-profile-container" data-category-list="business-tech ">

	
	<div class="g50-profile g50-profile--tony-bova" >

		<!-- label (like for sponsors) -->
		
		<!-- person's name -->
		<h2 class="g50-profile__name">
			<span>Tony Bova</span>
		</h2>

		<!-- person's position & city -->
					<div class="g50-profile__stats"><p>CEO, MOBIUS PBC<br />
KNOXVILLE, TENNESSEE</p>
</div>
		
		<!-- person's excerpt -->
		<h3 class="g50-profile__excerpt"><p>This chemist has the solution for a more fantastic plastic</p>
</h3>

		<!-- guest author stuff -->
		
		<!-- person's photo -->
					<div class="g50-profile__photo">
				<img src="https://grist.files.wordpress.com/2020/03/tony-bova-1.jpg?w=560" class="g50-profile__photo-img wp-post-image" alt="" data-noattr="1" srcset="https://grist.files.wordpress.com/2020/03/tony-bova-1.jpg?w=560 560w, https://grist.files.wordpress.com/2020/03/tony-bova-1.jpg?w=1120 1120w, https://grist.files.wordpress.com/2020/03/tony-bova-1.jpg?w=330 330w, https://grist.files.wordpress.com/2020/03/tony-bova-1.jpg?w=768 768w" sizes="(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px" />				<!-- photo credit -->
									<p class="g50-profile__photo-credit">Photo: <a href="http://ww.malloryladd.com" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Mallory Ladd</a></p>
							</div>
		
		<!-- person's content -->
		<div class="g50-profile__body">
			<p>As a chemist, Tony Bova always wanted to make stuff. But he wanted to make <em>better</em> stuff — stuff that might actually solve problems, not just clog up landfills.</p>
<p>He hit upon a plan to turn a paper-industry waste product called lignan into a bioplastic that degrades after its usefulness is over. In 2016, with little more than “two beards and a pitch deck,” Bova and his hirsute business partner launched Mobius, which has since won 19 business competitions. Next comes fundraising, so they can produce at scale the chocolate-sprinkle-like “pellets” that are the building blocks of the plastics industry.</p>
<p>The first target: single-use, agriculture industry products like plastic flowerpots — over 5 billion of them are sold every year in the U.S. alone. The vision, he says, is to “turn organic waste resources into the chemicals of the future.”</p>
			<div class="g50-follow g50-follow--hide-desktop">
				<a class="g50-follow__link" href="https://twitter.com/bova_fett?lang=en" rel="noopener" target="_blank"><i class="fab fa-twitter g50-follow__icon"></i>Follow Tony Bova</a>			</div>
		</div>

