<div id="maeve-higgins" class="js-filtered-profile g50-profile-container" data-category-list="arts-media ">

	
	<div class="g50-profile g50-profile--maeve-higgins" >

		<!-- label (like for sponsors) -->
		
		<!-- person's name -->
		<h2 class="g50-profile__name">
			<span>Maeve Higgins</span>
		</h2>

		<!-- person's position & city -->
					<div class="g50-profile__stats"><p>WRITER &amp; PODCASTER<br />
BROOKLYN, NEW YORK</p>
</div>
		
		<!-- person's excerpt -->
		<h3 class="g50-profile__excerpt"><p>No joke: She knows the climate crisis is no time for despair</p>
</h3>

		<!-- guest author stuff -->
		
		<!-- person's photo -->
					<div class="g50-profile__photo">
				<img src="https://grist.files.wordpress.com/2020/03/maeve-higgins-1.jpg?w=560" class="g50-profile__photo-img wp-post-image" alt="" data-noattr="1" srcset="https://grist.files.wordpress.com/2020/03/maeve-higgins-1.jpg?w=560 560w, https://grist.files.wordpress.com/2020/03/maeve-higgins-1.jpg?w=1120 1120w, https://grist.files.wordpress.com/2020/03/maeve-higgins-1.jpg?w=330 330w, https://grist.files.wordpress.com/2020/03/maeve-higgins-1.jpg?w=768 768w" sizes="(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px" />				<!-- photo credit -->
									<p class="g50-profile__photo-credit">Photo: First Look Media</p>
							</div>
		
		<!-- person's content -->
		<div class="g50-profile__body">
			<p>For years, Maeve Higgins felt paralyzed about the climate crisis. As a writer and comedian, what could she do? When she heard that Mary Robinson, the former Irish president and former U.N. High Commissioner for Human Rights, was starting a podcast to highlight women across the world creating climate solutions and was looking for a cohost, Higgins jumped at the chance. For that show, Mothers of Invention, the duo interview people like a Vietnamese eco-fashion designer and Costa Rican diplomat Christiana Figueres. It’s definitely not stand-up comedy, but it is lighthearted. Comedians can show the full array of emotions, says Higgins: “That’s how I can help.”</p>
<p>Higgins is also an opinion writer for the New York Times, where she frequently discusses immigration — and the climate chaos that will, undoubtedly, increase the difficulties and number of refugees. But wallowing in despair won’t get you anywhere, she says: “It’s part of being human, that in dark times you’ll find camaraderie and something to giggle at.”</p>
			<div class="g50-follow g50-follow--hide-desktop">
				<a class="g50-follow__link" href="https://twitter.com/maevehiggins" rel="noopener" target="_blank"><i class="fab fa-twitter g50-follow__icon"></i>Follow Maeve Higgins</a>			</div>
		</div>

