<div id="michael-malcom" class="js-filtered-profile g50-profile-container" data-category-list="climate-energy policy-advocacy ">

	
	<div class="g50-profile g50-profile--michael-malcom" >

		<!-- label (like for sponsors) -->
					<div class="g50-profile__label">
				<i class="fas fa-circle g50-profile__label--icon" aria-hidden="true"></i> Member&#039;s Pick			</div>
		
		<!-- person's name -->
		<h2 class="g50-profile__name">
			<span>Michael Malcom</span>
		</h2>

		<!-- person's position & city -->
					<div class="g50-profile__stats"><p>EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR, PEOPLE'S JUSTICE COUNCIL<br />
BIRMINGHAM, ALABAMA</p>
</div>
		
		<!-- person's excerpt -->
		<h3 class="g50-profile__excerpt"><p>This pastor keeps the faith with climate justice</p>
</h3>

		<!-- guest author stuff -->
		
		<!-- person's photo -->
					<div class="g50-profile__photo">
				<img src="https://grist.files.wordpress.com/2020/03/michael-malcom-1.jpg?w=560" class="g50-profile__photo-img wp-post-image" alt="" data-noattr="1" srcset="https://grist.files.wordpress.com/2020/03/michael-malcom-1.jpg?w=560 560w, https://grist.files.wordpress.com/2020/03/michael-malcom-1.jpg?w=1120 1120w, https://grist.files.wordpress.com/2020/03/michael-malcom-1.jpg?w=330 330w, https://grist.files.wordpress.com/2020/03/michael-malcom-1.jpg?w=768 768w" sizes="(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px" />				<!-- photo credit -->
									<p class="g50-profile__photo-credit">Photo: UGA</p>
							</div>
		
		<!-- person's content -->
		<div class="g50-profile__body">
			<p>At a conference three years ago, Reverend Michael Malcom heard a speech that “took his blinders off” regarding how climate change was already affecting his congregants. Another pastor, Reverend Dr. Gerald Durley, described the disconnect he’d experienced preaching to his congregation in Atlanta: How can I preach in the pulpit, shout them in the pews, but they can’t breathe in public! Inspired by these words, Malcom launched the People’s Justice Council (PJC) in 2018 to “answer the prophetic call of speaking truth to power.”</p>
<p>The council unites faith leaders from many different organizations — Fridays for Future, 350.org — in the fight for environmental justice. Malcom runs the local chapter for Alabama Interfaith Power and Light, raising awareness around renewable energy from a perspective of faith, and he is also the U.S. liaison for the Climate Action Network, organizing climate strikes throughout Alabama. His efforts are just part of his faith, he says: “I hear God clearly in this space, so for me it’s a form of worship.”</p>
			<div class="g50-follow g50-follow--hide-desktop">
				<a class="g50-follow__link" href="https://twitter.com/mtmalcom" rel="noopener" target="_blank"><i class="fab fa-twitter g50-follow__icon"></i>Follow Michael Malcom</a>			</div>
		</div>

		<!-- person's cagetgories -->
		<div class="g50-profile__categories">
			<span>Category: </span>
												<button data-category="climate-energy">
						Climate &amp; Energy					</button>
																							<button data-category="policy-advocacy">
						Policy &amp; Advocacy					</button>
									</div>

