<div id="corina-newsome" class="js-filtered-profile g50-profile-container" data-category-list="arts-media policy-advocacy ">

	
	<div class="g50-profile g50-profile--corina-newsome" >

		<!-- label (like for sponsors) -->
		
		<!-- person's name -->
		<h2 class="g50-profile__name">
			<span>Corina Newsome</span>
		</h2>

		<!-- person's position & city -->
					<div class="g50-profile__stats"><p>GRADUATE STUDENT, GEORGIA SOUTHERN UNIVERSITY<br />
STATESBORO, GEORGIA</p>
</div>
		
		<!-- person's excerpt -->
		<h3 class="g50-profile__excerpt"><p>For her, a more inclusive green movement is just natural</p>
</h3>

		<!-- guest author stuff -->
		
		<!-- person's photo -->
					<div class="g50-profile__photo">
				<img src="https://grist.files.wordpress.com/2020/03/corina-newsome-1.jpg?w=560" class="g50-profile__photo-img wp-post-image" alt="" data-noattr="1" srcset="https://grist.files.wordpress.com/2020/03/corina-newsome-1.jpg?w=560 560w, https://grist.files.wordpress.com/2020/03/corina-newsome-1.jpg?w=1120 1120w, https://grist.files.wordpress.com/2020/03/corina-newsome-1.jpg?w=330 330w, https://grist.files.wordpress.com/2020/03/corina-newsome-1.jpg?w=768 768w" sizes="(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px" />				<!-- photo credit -->
									<p class="g50-profile__photo-credit">Photo: Katherine Arntzen</p>
							</div>
		
		<!-- person's content -->
		<div class="g50-profile__body">
			<p>When she was in her first year of college, a zookeeper gave Corina Newsome a peek behind the scenes. Newsome, who grew up in urban Philly, had never even visited a zoo before. That visit opened her eyes to the joy of a career with animals, and the realization that she could do it, too — the zookeeper was a black woman, just like Newsome.</p>
<p>As a zookeeper in Nashville, Tennessee, she created a Pathway to Animal Care Careers program for underrepresented high school students to get the chance she got. Now a graduate student studying sparrows, she’s also part of Young Evangelicals for Climate Action, which mobilizes the faithful on the issue. But she might be best known for her strong Twitter game, exploring issues involving systemic racism and conservation: “Social activism is very central to my faith,” she says.</p>
			<div class="g50-follow g50-follow--hide-desktop">
				<a class="g50-follow__link" href="https://twitter.com/hood_naturalist" rel="noopener" target="_blank"><i class="fab fa-twitter g50-follow__icon"></i>Follow Corina Newsome</a>			</div>
		</div>

		<!-- person's cagetgories -->
		<div class="g50-profile__categories">
			<span>Category: </span>
												<button data-category="arts-media">
						Arts &amp; Media					</button>
																							<button data-category="policy-advocacy">
						Policy &amp; Advocacy					</button>
									</div>

		<div class="g50-profile__footer">
			<div class="g50-follow g50-follow--hide-mobile">
				<a class="g50-follow__link" href="https://twitter.com/hood_naturalist" rel="noopener" target="_blank"><i class="fab fa-twitter g50-follow__icon"></i>Follow Corina Newsome</a>			</div>

