<div id="julian-brave-noisecat" class="js-filtered-profile g50-profile-container" data-category-list="arts-media policy-advocacy ">

	
	<div class="g50-profile g50-profile--julian-brave-noisecat" >

		<!-- label (like for sponsors) -->
		
		<!-- person's name -->
		<h2 class="g50-profile__name">
			<span>Julian Brave NoiseCat</span>
		</h2>

		<!-- person's position & city -->
					<div class="g50-profile__stats"><p>VP OF POLICY &amp; STRATEGY, DATA FOR PROGRESS<br />
WASHINGTON, D.C. </p>
</div>
		
		<!-- person's excerpt -->
		<h3 class="g50-profile__excerpt"><p>This writer explains the past — and heralds a better future</p>
</h3>

		<!-- guest author stuff -->
		
		<!-- person's photo -->
					<div class="g50-profile__photo">
				<img src="https://grist.files.wordpress.com/2020/03/julian-brave-noisecat-1.jpg?w=560" class="g50-profile__photo-img wp-post-image" alt="" data-noattr="1" srcset="https://grist.files.wordpress.com/2020/03/julian-brave-noisecat-1.jpg?w=560 560w, https://grist.files.wordpress.com/2020/03/julian-brave-noisecat-1.jpg?w=1120 1120w, https://grist.files.wordpress.com/2020/03/julian-brave-noisecat-1.jpg?w=330 330w, https://grist.files.wordpress.com/2020/03/julian-brave-noisecat-1.jpg?w=768 768w" sizes="(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px" />				<!-- photo credit -->
									<p class="g50-profile__photo-credit">Photo: Dante Garcia</p>
							</div>
		
		<!-- person's content -->
		<div class="g50-profile__body">
			<p>As a policy analyst who also “does words,” Julian Brave NoiseCat (Secwépemc and Stitlimx&#8217;) helps run a think tank called Data for Progress. There, he researches and stitches together policy ideas for projects like the Green New Deal and legislation to retrofit and decarbonize aging and highly polluting public housing. NoiseCat also wields words in essays that explore the power dynamics that underpin our collective “natural history” for the Natural History Museum, an arts and activism nonprofit (<a href="https://grist.org/grist-50/2020/#beka-economopoulos">the group’s founder</a> is also on the Grist 50 this year).</p>
<p>When he’s not doing policy work, NoiseCat writes articles for outlets like Harper’s and the New York Times. “Indigenous communities have faced the loss of our world before,” NoiseCat says. “That positions us uniquely to make a broader contribution to humanity, in the context of a climate crisis that requires us to rethink our relationship to the planet.”</p>
			<div class="g50-follow g50-follow--hide-desktop">
				<a class="g50-follow__link" href="https://twitter.com/jnoisecat" rel="noopener" target="_blank"><i class="fab fa-twitter g50-follow__icon"></i>Follow Julian Brave NoiseCat</a>			</div>
		</div>

		<!-- person's cagetgories -->
