<div id="nathan-proctor" class="js-filtered-profile g50-profile-container" data-category-list="business-tech ">

	
	<div class="g50-profile g50-profile--nathan-proctor" >

		<!-- label (like for sponsors) -->
		
		<!-- person's name -->
		<h2 class="g50-profile__name">
			<span>Nathan Proctor</span>
		</h2>

		<!-- person's position & city -->
					<div class="g50-profile__stats"><p>NATIONAL CAMPAIGN DIRECTOR, RIGHT TO REPAIR, U.S. PIRG<br />
BOSTON, MASSACHUSETTS</p>
</div>
		
		<!-- person's excerpt -->
		<h3 class="g50-profile__excerpt"><p>He wants to help you fix your broken tech</p>
</h3>

		<!-- guest author stuff -->
		
		<!-- person's photo -->
					<div class="g50-profile__photo">
				<img src="https://grist.files.wordpress.com/2020/03/nathan-proctor-1.jpg?w=560" class="g50-profile__photo-img wp-post-image" alt="" data-noattr="1" srcset="https://grist.files.wordpress.com/2020/03/nathan-proctor-1.jpg?w=560 560w, https://grist.files.wordpress.com/2020/03/nathan-proctor-1.jpg?w=1120 1120w, https://grist.files.wordpress.com/2020/03/nathan-proctor-1.jpg?w=330 330w, https://grist.files.wordpress.com/2020/03/nathan-proctor-1.jpg?w=768 768w" sizes="(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px" />				<!-- photo credit -->
									<p class="g50-profile__photo-credit">Photo: Kimball Nelson</p>
							</div>
		
		<!-- person's content -->
		<div class="g50-profile__body">
			<p>Our electronics create a mountain of junk, says Nathan Proctor — when the iPhone 6 was being manufactured, for example, each one required more raw materials than a dishwasher. And then they become junk themselves: Americans toss 416,000 cell phones in the trash each day.</p>
<p>One solution? Make those gadgets last longer by allowing people to repair their own. Yet most tech giants have made that impossible, citing safety or cyber-security risks. Proctor is pushing for state and local laws that would ensure customers have the right to fix their stuff without having to use official (and often pricey) company channels like Apple&#8217;s Genius Bar.</p>
<p>Legislation has been introduced in 22 states. While tech companies, collectively worth trillions of dollars, are pushing back, if just one law passes, Proctor says, “the dam will burst.”</p>
			<div class="g50-follow g50-follow--hide-desktop">
				<a class="g50-follow__link" href="https://twitter.com/nProctor" rel="noopener" target="_blank"><i class="fab fa-twitter g50-follow__icon"></i>Follow Nathan Proctor</a>			</div>
		</div>

