<div id="emily-rice" class="js-filtered-profile g50-profile-container" data-category-list="climate-energy ">

	
	<div class="g50-profile g50-profile--emily-rice" >

		<!-- label (like for sponsors) -->
		
		<!-- person's name -->
		<h2 class="g50-profile__name">
			<span>Emily Rice</span>
		</h2>

		<!-- person's position & city -->
					<div class="g50-profile__stats"><p>CHIEF OPERATING OFFICER, THE ENERGY GROUP CO., INC.<br />
DES MOINES, IOWA</p>
</div>
		
		<!-- person's excerpt -->
		<h3 class="g50-profile__excerpt"><p>She’s building a more efficient Midwest</p>
</h3>

		<!-- guest author stuff -->
		
		<!-- person's photo -->
					<div class="g50-profile__photo">
				<img src="https://grist.files.wordpress.com/2020/03/emily-rice-1.jpg?w=560" class="g50-profile__photo-img wp-post-image" alt="" data-noattr="1" srcset="https://grist.files.wordpress.com/2020/03/emily-rice-1.jpg?w=560 560w, https://grist.files.wordpress.com/2020/03/emily-rice-1.jpg?w=1120 1120w, https://grist.files.wordpress.com/2020/03/emily-rice-1.jpg?w=330 330w, https://grist.files.wordpress.com/2020/03/emily-rice-1.jpg?w=768 768w" sizes="(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px" />				<!-- photo credit -->
									<p class="g50-profile__photo-credit">Photo: Nicole Trower</p>
							</div>
		
		<!-- person's content -->
		<div class="g50-profile__body">
			<p>Shiny solar panels and fields of wind turbines get most of the attention, but fine-tuning old building stock and ensuring new structures are built as energy-efficiently as possible are also powerful buffers against carbon emissions. “The connection between building infrastructure and climate change is pretty profound,” says Emily Rice. Plus, upgrading buildings improves the economy.</p>
<p>At The Energy Group, which offers energy-savings services throughout the Midwest, Rice manages an evaluation process that focuses on how people actually <em>use</em> the buildings in question. Then her team comes up with solutions to lower costs, such as recommending new, more efficient equipment that can also boost the bottom line. “Sustainable practices have often been at odds with business,” she says. “But with energy efficiency, we know that’s not true.”</p>
			<div class="g50-follow g50-follow--hide-desktop">
				<a class="g50-follow__link" href="https://twitter.com/The_Emily_Show" rel="noopener" target="_blank"><i class="fab fa-twitter g50-follow__icon"></i>Follow Emily Rice</a>			</div>
		</div>

