<div id="ian-skor" class="js-filtered-profile g50-profile-container" data-category-list="business-tech food-farming ">

	
	<div class="g50-profile g50-profile--ian-skor" >

		<!-- label (like for sponsors) -->
		
		<!-- person's name -->
		<h2 class="g50-profile__name">
			<span>Ian Skor</span>
		</h2>

		<!-- person's position & city -->
					<div class="g50-profile__stats"><p>COFOUNDER, SANDBOX SOLAR<br />
FORT COLLINS, COLORADO</p>
</div>
		
		<!-- person's excerpt -->
		<h3 class="g50-profile__excerpt"><p>He’s planting a new idea on solar fields</p>
</h3>

		<!-- guest author stuff -->
		
		<!-- person's photo -->
					<div class="g50-profile__photo">
				<img src="https://grist.files.wordpress.com/2020/03/ian-skor-1.jpg?w=560" class="g50-profile__photo-img wp-post-image" alt="" data-noattr="1" srcset="https://grist.files.wordpress.com/2020/03/ian-skor-1.jpg?w=560 560w, https://grist.files.wordpress.com/2020/03/ian-skor-1.jpg?w=1120 1120w, https://grist.files.wordpress.com/2020/03/ian-skor-1.jpg?w=330 330w, https://grist.files.wordpress.com/2020/03/ian-skor-1.jpg?w=768 768w" sizes="(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px" />				<!-- photo credit -->
							</div>
		
		<!-- person's content -->
		<div class="g50-profile__body">
			<p>About five years ago, Ian Skor started Sandbox Solar out of his car, with zero dollars and a plan to become the local go-to for all things solar. Now, one of his big ideas is playing out in partnership with Colorado State University.</p>
<p>“Land is so difficult to find here that’s affordable for solar and affordable for food production,” Skor says. His brainwave: Combine the two. Cropland is ideal for solar panels, since wide-open fields soak up plenty of sun without getting so hot that panels overheat. Meanwhile, the partial shade furnished by panels can conserve water (and make cool-loving plants like kale and spinach happier).</p>
<p>Now the leading rooftop-panel installer in Northern Colorado, Sandbox Solar also dabbles in off-grid solar, battery backup, smart grids, and electric-vehicle charging stations. Yes, it’s a lot, Skor admits: “We have a knack for picking the most difficult projects.”</p>
			<div class="g50-follow g50-follow--hide-desktop">
				<a class="g50-follow__link" href="https://www.instagram.com/sandboxsolar/" rel="noopener" target="_blank"><i class="fab fa-instagram g50-follow__icon"></i>Follow Sandbox Solar</a>			</div>
		</div>

