<div id="geoffrey-supran" class="js-filtered-profile g50-profile-container" data-category-list="climate-energy ">

	
	<div class="g50-profile g50-profile--geoffrey-supran" >

		<!-- label (like for sponsors) -->
		
		<!-- person's name -->
		<h2 class="g50-profile__name">
			<span>Geoffrey Supran</span>
		</h2>

		<!-- person's position & city -->
					<div class="g50-profile__stats"><p>RESEARCH ASSOCIATE, HARVARD UNIVERSITY<br />
BOSTON, MASSACHUSETTS</p>
</div>
		
		<!-- person's excerpt -->
		<h3 class="g50-profile__excerpt"><p>This activist scientist turns up the heat on Big Oil</p>
</h3>

		<!-- guest author stuff -->
		
		<!-- person's photo -->
					<div class="g50-profile__photo">
				<img src="https://grist.files.wordpress.com/2020/03/geoffrey-supran-1.jpg?w=560" class="g50-profile__photo-img wp-post-image" alt="" data-noattr="1" srcset="https://grist.files.wordpress.com/2020/03/geoffrey-supran-1.jpg?w=560 560w, https://grist.files.wordpress.com/2020/03/geoffrey-supran-1.jpg?w=1120 1120w, https://grist.files.wordpress.com/2020/03/geoffrey-supran-1.jpg?w=330 330w, https://grist.files.wordpress.com/2020/03/geoffrey-supran-1.jpg?w=768 768w" sizes="(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px" />				<!-- photo credit -->
									<p class="g50-profile__photo-credit">Photo: Audrey Eyring</p>
							</div>
		
		<!-- person's content -->
		<div class="g50-profile__body">
			<p>As a scientist, Geoffrey Supran always knew his renewable-energy research was important to humanity’s future. But it was a 2012 article about the moral consequences of climate change that shook him to his core. He realized he had to act.</p>
<p>So began Supran’s journey from academic to activist. That meant on-the-ground protests — among other actions, Supran co-led a campaign to get MIT to ditch fossil fuel investments. It also meant research, such as a 2017 paper that blew the lid off ExxonMobil’s climate-change misinformation campaign, and was so widely covered that it reached an estimated half-billion people worldwide.</p>
<p>Supran has testified as an expert witness on the oil and gas industries’ history of denial and obfuscation for policymakers and helped organize the first science marches against Trump. Now, he wants the rest of his peers to get involved. “Orthodoxy says there&#8217;s a firewall between academia and activism,” he says. “I’m focused on mobilizing scientists and scientific institutions to be braver.”</p>
			<div class="g50-follow g50-follow--hide-desktop">
				<a class="g50-follow__link" href="https://twitter.com/GeoffreySupran" rel="noopener" target="_blank"><i class="fab fa-twitter g50-follow__icon"></i>Follow Geoffrey Supran</a>			</div>
		</div>

		<!-- person's cagetgories -->
		<div class="g50-profile__categories">
