<div id="evelyn-valdez-ward" class="js-filtered-profile g50-profile-container" data-category-list="policy-advocacy ">

	
	<div class="g50-profile g50-profile--evelyn-valdez-ward" >

		<!-- label (like for sponsors) -->
		
		<!-- person's name -->
		<h2 class="g50-profile__name">
			<span>Evelyn Valdez-Ward</span>
		</h2>

		<!-- person's position & city -->
					<div class="g50-profile__stats"><p>PHD CANDIDATE, UNIVERSITY OF CALIFORNIA, IRVINE<br />
NEWPORT BEACH, CALIFORNIA</p>
</div>
		
		<!-- person's excerpt -->
		<h3 class="g50-profile__excerpt"><p>This scientist is working on a new formula for justice</p>
</h3>

		<!-- guest author stuff -->
		
		<!-- person's photo -->
					<div class="g50-profile__photo">
				<img src="https://grist.files.wordpress.com/2020/03/evelyn-valdez-ward-1.jpg?w=560" class="g50-profile__photo-img wp-post-image" alt="" data-noattr="1" srcset="https://grist.files.wordpress.com/2020/03/evelyn-valdez-ward-1.jpg?w=560 560w, https://grist.files.wordpress.com/2020/03/evelyn-valdez-ward-1.jpg?w=1120 1120w, https://grist.files.wordpress.com/2020/03/evelyn-valdez-ward-1.jpg?w=330 330w, https://grist.files.wordpress.com/2020/03/evelyn-valdez-ward-1.jpg?w=768 768w" sizes="(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px" />				<!-- photo credit -->
							</div>
		
		<!-- person's content -->
		<div class="g50-profile__body">
			<p>It wasn’t until she applied for college that Evelyn Valdez-Ward, a self-described “nerd” who arrived in the U.S. as an infant, learned she was undocumented. Thanks to DACA and hard work, Valdez-Ward got through undergrad and to a PhD program at UC Irvine. But funding for her research, on how microbes help plants cope with climate change, was hard to get. Most research dollars are handed out at the federal level — to citizens only.</p>
<p>Frustration bore fruit in the form of Reclaiming STEM, a workshop Valdez-Ward cofounded for scientists from diverse and underrepresented groups. Hundreds of participants have attended so far, discussing topics like social justice, identity, and how to use social media to advocate for change. There are more sessions coming in the Bay Area and in Boston later this year. Her driving question: “How can we change policies that are making science so exclusive?”</p>
			<div class="g50-follow g50-follow--hide-desktop">
				<a class="g50-follow__link" href="https://twitter.com/wardofplants" rel="noopener" target="_blank"><i class="fab fa-twitter g50-follow__icon"></i>Follow Evelyn Valdez-Ward</a>			</div>
		</div>

		<!-- person's cagetgories -->
