<div id="jason-ward" class="js-filtered-profile g50-profile-container" data-category-list="arts-media ">

	
	<div class="g50-profile g50-profile--jason-ward" >

		<!-- label (like for sponsors) -->
		
		<!-- person's name -->
		<h2 class="g50-profile__name">
			<span>Jason Ward</span>
		</h2>

		<!-- person's position & city -->
					<div class="g50-profile__stats"><p>HOST, BIRDS OF NORTH AMERICA<br />
ATLANTA, GEORGIA</p>
</div>
		
		<!-- person's excerpt -->
		<h3 class="g50-profile__excerpt"><p>This birdwatcher is known for his tweets</p>
</h3>

		<!-- guest author stuff -->
		
		<!-- person's photo -->
					<div class="g50-profile__photo">
				<img src="https://grist.files.wordpress.com/2020/03/jason-ward-1.jpg?w=560" class="g50-profile__photo-img wp-post-image" alt="" data-noattr="1" srcset="https://grist.files.wordpress.com/2020/03/jason-ward-1.jpg?w=560 560w, https://grist.files.wordpress.com/2020/03/jason-ward-1.jpg?w=1120 1120w, https://grist.files.wordpress.com/2020/03/jason-ward-1.jpg?w=330 330w, https://grist.files.wordpress.com/2020/03/jason-ward-1.jpg?w=768 768w" sizes="(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px" />				<!-- photo credit -->
							</div>
		
		<!-- person's content -->
		<div class="g50-profile__body">
			<p>One of Jason Ward’s early birdwatching thrills was seeing a peregrine falcon ripping into a pigeon, right outside the window of the Bronx homeless shelter that his family was staying in. As a child, he idolized TV wildlife experts Steve Irwin and Jeff Corwin, but it never occurred to him that one day he, too, could have a career celebrating wildlife and teaching people about it.</p>
<p>Later, as a young adult, he started birding for real. Within months, he was leading weekend field trips for Atlanta Audubon. On social media, his enthusiasm, expertise, and humor led to an invitation to launch a web series for Topic about birdwatching, <a href="https://www.topic.com/birds-of-north-america" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Birds of North America</a>, that has hundreds of thousands of views. He now has that dream job, just like Irwin or Corwin. “It’s about opening doors, and allowing people to share what I already know: These animals are amazing, and they’re everywhere,” he says.</p>
			<div class="g50-follow g50-follow--hide-desktop">
				<a class="g50-follow__link" href="https://twitter.com/JasonWardNY" rel="noopener" target="_blank"><i class="fab fa-twitter g50-follow__icon"></i>Follow Jason Ward</a>			</div>
		</div>

		<!-- person's cagetgories -->
		<div class="g50-profile__categories">
			<span>Category: </span>
												<button data-category="arts-media">
						Arts &amp; Media					</button>
																</div>

