<div id="thanushka-yakupitiyage" class="js-filtered-profile g50-profile-container" data-category-list="policy-advocacy ">

	
	<div class="g50-profile g50-profile--thanushka-yakupitiyage" >

		<!-- label (like for sponsors) -->
		
		<!-- person's name -->
		<h2 class="g50-profile__name">
			<span>Thanushka Yakupitiyage</span>
		</h2>

		<!-- person's position & city -->
					<div class="g50-profile__stats"><p>U.S. COMMUNICATIONS DIRECTOR, 350.ORG<br />
BROOKLYN, NEW YORK</p>
</div>
		
		<!-- person's excerpt -->
		<h3 class="g50-profile__excerpt"><p>She brings migrant might to the climate fight</p>
</h3>

		<!-- guest author stuff -->
		
		<!-- person's photo -->
					<div class="g50-profile__photo">
				<img src="https://grist.files.wordpress.com/2020/03/thanu-yakupitiyage-1.jpg?w=560" class="g50-profile__photo-img wp-post-image" alt="" data-noattr="1" srcset="https://grist.files.wordpress.com/2020/03/thanu-yakupitiyage-1.jpg?w=560 560w, https://grist.files.wordpress.com/2020/03/thanu-yakupitiyage-1.jpg?w=1120 1120w, https://grist.files.wordpress.com/2020/03/thanu-yakupitiyage-1.jpg?w=330 330w, https://grist.files.wordpress.com/2020/03/thanu-yakupitiyage-1.jpg?w=768 768w" sizes="(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px" />				<!-- photo credit -->
									<p class="g50-profile__photo-credit">Photo: Tavish Timothy</p>
							</div>
		
		<!-- person's content -->
		<div class="g50-profile__body">
			<p>After college, Thanushka Yakupitiyage was a researcher for Rinku Sen’s book <em>The Accidental American</em>, which details how families of undocumented workers in the Twin Towers lost out on 9/11 compensation because of their immigration status. It was later, when she was hired at the New York Immigration Coalition, that she joined the climate fight. “Climate and immigration are inherently linked … with black and brown communities the most vulnerable,” she says, “and yet the U.S. climate movement is still very white.”</p>
<p>Now, as U.S. communications director at 350.org, Yakupitiyage focuses on multi-racial coalition-building and ensuring the climate movement considers migrant rights. She mobilizes protests at climate summits and mentors young people of color to be the “best spokespeople they can be.” She’s also an artist and DJ, for the same reason she fights for immigrants and a healthy climate: &#8220;People power.&#8221;</p>
			<div class="g50-follow g50-follow--hide-desktop">
				<a class="g50-follow__link" href="https://twitter.com/ty_ushka" rel="noopener" target="_blank"><i class="fab fa-twitter g50-follow__icon"></i>Follow Thanushka Yakupitiyage</a>			</div>
		</div>

		<!-- person's cagetgories -->
		<div class="g50-profile__categories">
			<span>Category: </span>
																			<button data-category="policy-advocacy">
						Policy &amp; Advocacy					</button>
									</div>

		<div class="g50-profile__footer">
			<div class="g50-follow g50-follow--hide-mobile">
				<a class="g50-follow__link" href="https://twitter.com/ty_ushka" rel="noopener" target="_blank"><i class="fab fa-twitter g50-follow__icon"></i>Follow Thanushka Yakupitiyage</a>			</div>

